early forecast. More conservative on Bernie in this state. Florida democratic primary electorate is quite a bit older than the nation as a whole, with more black voters: both those facts should favour Biden. Clinton won one of her bigger victories vs Sanders here in 2016. On the flip side, there is also a substantial (20% +) Latino voting base, which wasn't a strong support base for Sanders in 2016, but judging from Nevada he seems to have won over in 2020. Of course I predict strong momentum on Bernie's side and it's not clear if Biden will even be in the race by then.

For this forecast, I used the crowd forecast, the prediction market [1] and the latest state poll (if available) reported in RealClear Politics [2]. I scaled the forecast to the top 3 candidatesonly. [1] https://www.predictit.org/markets/detail/6040 [2] https://www.realclearpolitics.com/
